   {:e #blake3 "9999822dace93c53d29caf10574b8fdb196e43e885721001bd12cd3ca80f1cac" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-f0b04ff07d2f11a0; Session entity: :task/t-b90503c9; Session entity: :recon/trace-0ee92fa66a85f94a; Session entity: :recon/trace-fd134942dcce7c20; Session entity: :task/t-c9672448; Session entity: :recon/trace-f7414e4ff4ae677a; Session entity: :recon/trace-e324651be197474f; LIVESTORE PLAN REVISION (Session 039 deep review): Five architectural gaps found. (1) INIT PATH: LiveStore::open() fails on non-existent .braid. Need LiveStore::create(path) for braid init — creates DiskLayout, writes genesis+schema txn files, then constructs LiveStore from the new store. This is the bootstrap path. (2) DIRTY FLAG OPTIMIZATION: Serializing store.bin on EVERY write_tx adds N*100ms per command. harvest does 5+ writes = 500ms of serialization. Fix: LiveStore tracks dirty:bool flag. write_tx marks dirty=true but does NOT serialize. LiveStore::flush() serializes if dirty. Drop impl calls flush(). Commands that need cache fresh for another process (status returning to agent) call flush() explicitly. This reduces serialization from N-per-command to 1-per-command. (3) STALE CACHE HOTFIX URGENCY: The fitness.json/coherence.json bugs are LIVE RIGHT NOW. LIVESTORE-HOTFIX (t-449ec46d) should be implemented BEFORE any LiveStore work. (4) BACKWARD COMPAT: Old store.bin files must remain readable after LiveStore deployment. Add a test that deserializes a known-good store.bin from the current system. (5) E2E LOGGING: LIVESTORE-TEST E2E script needs structured logging with timestamps at every assertion point so failures show exactly WHERE and WHEN things broke, not just that they broke.; Session entity: :recon/trace-20a9380425e93784; Session entity: :recon/trace-47ebaf4d5c104b0e; Session entity: :recon/trace-f22d3a07bd3a6cc3; Session entity: :recon/trace-a365251f88985f02\nSession entity: :task/t-1250a47c; Write-Through Batching; Session entity: :task/t-d73f